Executive Profile
Richard H. Auchinleck  Independent Chairman, TELUS CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships65C$507,826
Background

		Mr. Richard H. Auchinleck, also known as Dick, served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Gulf Canada Resources Limited (now known as ConocoPhillips Canada Resources Corp.) from 1998 until its acquisition by Conoco in 2001. Mr. Auchinleck served as a Chief Operating Officer of Gulf Canada from 1997 to 1998 and Chief Executive Officer for Gulf Indonesia Resources Limited from 1997 to 1998. Mr. Auchinleck serves as Lead Director of ConocoPhillips and has been its ... Independent Director since August 2002. He has been an Independent Chairman of Telus Corporation since August 10, 2015 and has been its Director since 2003. He has been an Independent Director of TELUS Communications Inc., since 2003 and also serves as a Trustee of Enbridge Commercial Trust. He serves as Director of ConocoPhillips Co., Inc. Mr. Auchinleck began his service as a Director of Conoco Inc. in 2001 prior to its merger with Phillips Petroleum Company in 2002. He previously served on the board of Red Mile Entertainment Inc., from 2005 to 2008 and also served as a Director of Hydro One Limited. He served as an Independent Director of Enbridge Income Fund Holdings Inc., since December 17, 2010 until November 3, 2014. He also served as a Director of ConocoPhillips Alaska, Inc. and ConocoPhillips (U.K.) Limited. He is a Founding Director and Lifetime Member of the Canadian Heavy Oil Association and a Member of the Association of Professional Engineers, Geologists and Geophysicists of Alberta. Mr. Auchinleck holds a Bachelor of Applied Science Degree in Chemical Engineering from the University of British Columbia in 1976.Read Full Background




